dmca.title: Bat World Sanctuary et al vs Cummins
dmca.body:
"On the 4th day of May, 2011 came on to be heard the application for a temporary injunction filed by the plaintiffs.The plaintiffs appeared by and through their attorney of record. The defendant, Mary Cummins, appeared in person.

It is therefore ordered that Mary Cummins immediately remove from the internet all of the materials concerning Bat world Sanctuary and Amanda Lollar which have been posted or placed on the internet at the following URL's and locations:

140 URL links"

Note: Mary Cummins only controls three URLs. She only posted some photos, videos on Facebook, YouTube and Flickr. She posted these photos with written and oral permission from Lollar and Bat World. Cummins was sued three months after she posted the videos and photos. She was sued in retaliation for reporting Amanda Lollar and Bat World Sanctuary for animal cruelty, animal neglect, violations of the health code, violations of the Animal Welfare Act, performing surgery on animals without a veterinary permit...
